<font color="#FF0000">RULES FOR THE FUTURE</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 28 15:24:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I think it has to do with how you are brought up.  If your own mother took on all of the work of the home, then chances are you will simply fall into that trap as well.<br><br>
My hope for the next generation of boys/men is that they will see women struggling to help with financial family considerations, and realize that they cannot rely exclusively on them for all the home maintenance.  It may not mean that they will do a lot, but awareness will be built, and perhaps several generations down the road, we will have equality in the workplace and the home!
